<CSS_font-faceFont-style>
<summary>
The <strong><c>font-style</c></strong> CSS descriptor allows authors to specify font styles for the fonts specified in the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face">@font-face</see> at-rule.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>For a particular font family, authors can download various font faces that correspond to the different styles of the same font family and then use the <c>font-style</c> descriptor to explicitly specify the font face's style. The values for this CSS descriptor are the same as that of the corresponding <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/font-style">font-style</see> property.</para>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face/font-display">@font-face/font-display</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face/font-family">@font-face/font-family</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face/font-stretch">@font-face/font-stretch</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face/font-weight">@font-face/font-weight</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/font-feature-settings">font-feature-settings</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face/font-variation-settings">@font-face/font-variation-settings</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face/src">@font-face/src</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face/unicode-range">@font-face/unicode-range</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@font-face/font-style"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
